{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-docs-js","path":"/docs/postman-graphql-playground.html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; \" > <div class=\"video\"> <iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/27IHNDG4Kaw\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture\" allowfullscreen style=\" position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \"></iframe> </div> </div>\n<p>If you don’t already have a preference of your own, check out the ScandiPWA tool recommendations for testing, debugging and database management.</p>\n<p>Recommended tools:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/prisma-labs/graphql-playground\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">GraphQL Playground</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.postman.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Postman</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dbeaver.io/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">DBeaver</a> for Linux</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.sequelpro.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Sequel Pro</a> for Mac</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Topics covered:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#graphql-playground-features\">GraphQL Playground features</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#postman-features\">Postman features</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#database-management-tools\">Database management tools</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"graphql-playground-features\"><a href=\"#graphql-playground-features\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>GraphQL Playground Features</h2>\n<p>GraphQL Playground is an IDE for learning and using GraphQL. You can download the latest release for your platform of choice - Mac, Linux or Windows.</p>\n<p>Features:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ability to store schema, tabs and workspaces.</li>\n<li>‘DOCS’ section lets you preview GraphQL queries, type details and specific fields of a schema.</li>\n<li>\n<p>The ‘SCHEMA’ tab allows you to preview the GraphQL schema and download it as a file.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You can parse through ‘SCHEMA’ using regular expressions and search for ‘DOCS’ using the search field.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Ability to add multiple URLs</li>\n<li>‘PRETTIFY’ code feature</li>\n<li>Request history</li>\n<li>\n<p>Support for HTTP headers and query variables</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Send requests with HTTP headers by adding them as a JSON object in the ‘HTTP HEADERS’ section.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Drawbacks:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>No proper error handling</li>\n<li>If your GraphQL server responds with a non-json error you’ll see:</li>\n</ul>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"38577159497069720000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`&quot;error&quot;: &quot;Unexpected token < in JSON at position 0&quot;`, `38577159497069720000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"jsx\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-jsx\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-jsx\"><span class=\"token string\">\"error\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"Unexpected token &lt; in JSON at position 0\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>In this case you can ‘Inspect Element’ with the Inspector and you’ll see how the request is sent in the ‘Response’ and ‘Preview’ tab. In this case it’s:</li>\n</ul>\n<div\n              class=\"gatsby-code-button-container\"\n              data-toaster-id=\"19262756769038127000\"\n              data-toaster-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster customToasterClass\"\n              data-toaster-text-class=\"gatsby-code-button-toaster-text customToasterTextClass\"\n              data-toaster-text=\"Copied\"\n              data-toaster-duration=\"3500\"\n              onClick=\"copyToClipboard(`502 Bad Gateway`, `19262756769038127000`)\"\n            >\n              <div\n                class=\"gatsby-code-button customButtonClass\"\n                data-tooltip=\"\"\n              >\n                Copy<svg class=\"gatsby-code-button-icon\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path fill=\"none\" d=\"M0 0h24v24H0V0z\"/><path d=\"M16 1H2v16h2V3h12V1zm-1 4l6 6v12H6V5h9zm-1 7h5.5L14 6.5V12z\"/></svg>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"gatsby-code-text\"><code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">502 Bad Gateway</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"postman-features\"><a href=\"#postman-features\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Postman Features</h2>\n<p>Postman is a user-friendly tool for API testing. If you’re not sure whether or not this tool is for you, just <code class=\"gatsby-code-text\">ctrl + F</code> your request <a href=\"https://www.postman.com/postman-features/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Some of the major features are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Test writing</p>\n<ul>\n<li>See the full error logs right away, not only for POST requests, but also for GET requests.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Executing multiple simultaneous requests</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Useful for finding bugs that happen radomly, i.e. in a specific period of time.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"database-management-tools\"><a href=\"#database-management-tools\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Database Management Tools</h2>\n<p>The team of ScandiPWA recommends <a href=\"https://dbeaver.io/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">DBeaver</a> for Linux. You can check out the user-guide <a href=\"https://github.com/dbeaver/dbeaver/wiki\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>MySQL database management application for Mac - <a href=\"https://www.sequelpro.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Sequel Pro</a>. Read how to get started <a href=\"https://sequelpro.com/docs\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Postman & GraphQL Playground"},"fields":{"path":"content/docs/postman-graphql-playground.md","slug":"/docs/postman-graphql-playground.html"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/docs/postman-graphql-playground.html"}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}